@<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">
<html>
<head>
   <title>Icosahedral Reconstructions</title>
</head>

<body>
<img src="icosa.jpg" align="left"> <img src="icosa2.jpg" align="right"> <br>
<br>

<h2 align="center">Icosahedral Reconstructions</h2> 

 <h2 align="center">in SPIDER</h2>

<br> <br> <br>
 
<ul>

<li>The reference structure has to be placed such that the 5-fold
    symmetry axis is on Z-axis.</li>
<p></p>

<li>Any refinement program (from <a href="./recon/mr.html">Three
    Dimensional Reconstruction of Single Particle Specimens using
    Reference Projections</a>) can be used with the following
    modifications:</li>
<p></p>

   <ul>
   <li>Alignment operations should not check mirrored positions
       (see <a href="../man/apsh.html">AP SH</a>)</li>

   <p></p>

   <li><a href="../man/voea.html">VO EA</a> operation that appears in
      these procedures has to be modified such that the unique triangle
      specified is:    <br />
      theta = 0,37     <br />
      phi   = 0,71.999 <br />
   </li>
   </ul>
<p></p>

<li>The 3D reconstruction operations need a icosahedral symmetry
   document file which is given below. Here is the same file for
   downloading: <a href="ico_symm.txt">ico_symm.txt</a></li>

<li>
<hr>
<h4>Iscosahedral Symmetries Document File</h4>

